# Never commit package-lock.json. The monorepo uses pnpm; the standalone
# public repo is run via `npm install` by users, who generate their own
# lockfile locally. A committed lockfile would pin them to whatever
# transitive versions resolved on the publishing machine — which is how
# npm ERESOLVE conflicts (e.g. vite-plugin-svelte 6.x vs 7.x peer-dep
# clashes) leak through to users.
app/package-lock.json
package-lock.json
data/*.json
!data/ice-cream-shop.json
!data/lawrence-corr-beam-bem.json
!data/saas-revenue-events-matrix-2.json
.DS_Store
.env
.env.*
*.log
